WEBVTT

1
00:00:48.080 --> 00:00:50.440
-Is it a girl?
- Yes.

2
00:00:50.520 --> 00:00:52.160
Show me its arm.

3
00:00:52.240 --> 00:00:55.000
- She bears the mark.
- No!

4
00:00:57.560 --> 00:01:00.920
The omen is true.
I must tell my mother.

5
00:01:03.240 --> 00:01:05.280
- Help me!
- I can't.

6
00:01:05.360 --> 00:01:08.040
- They're going to kill her.

7
00:01:15.600 --> 00:01:19.960
Oh. thank you. Ethna. Thank you.

8
00:01:28.120 --> 00:01:30.600
Stand aside for Queen Bavmorda!

9
00:01:53.960 --> 00:01:56.360
You cannot
stop the prophecy!

10
00:01:56.440 --> 00:01:59.240
This child will have no power over me.
Start the ritual.

11
00:01:59.320 --> 00:02:03.960
- No. No!
- Where's the baby?

12
00:02:04.040 --> 00:02:06.360
The midwife.
Find that baby. Sorsha.

13
00:02:06.440 --> 00:02:09.680
Use the dogs.
Bring her back to me alive!

14
00:02:09.720 --> 00:02:11.760
Your reign of terror
is at an end!

15
00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:13.840
She will come back.
and she will finish you!

16
00:02:13.920 --> 00:02:17.360
- Silence. wench.
- My baby will finish you!
- Kill her.

17
00:05:36.080 --> 00:05:38.000
Dada! Dada!

18
00:05:41.280 --> 00:05:44.440
-Dada! Dada!
- Whoa! Whoa!

19
00:05:45.640 --> 00:05:48.760
Dada! Dada!
We found something in the river.

20
00:05:48.800 --> 00:05:50.680
I can't run off and play
with you now. Ranon.

21
00:05:50.720 --> 00:05:52.920
- I've got work to do.
- You gotta come. Hurry!

22
00:05:57.720 --> 00:06:00.160
Come on.

23
00:06:02.400 --> 00:06:05.320
Don't go near it.
We don't know where it's been.

24
00:06:05.400 --> 00:06:08.200
But. Dada. it's a baby.

25
00:06:08.280 --> 00:06:12.880
- It's not like us.
- No. It's not a Nelwyn.

26
00:06:12.960 --> 00:06:16.360
- It looks like a Daikini baby.
- What's a Daikini?

27
00:06:16.440 --> 00:06:18.680
Daikinis are big.

28
00:06:18.720 --> 00:06:21.720
- Giants who live far away.

29
00:06:21.800 --> 00:06:24.000
Oh. she's so cute.

30
00:06:24.080 --> 00:06:27.960
- Can't we keep it. Dada?
- No!

31
00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:33.040
We'll push it downstream and forget
we ever saw it. Come on.

32
00:06:33.120 --> 00:06:34.960
- Come on.
- Ufgood! Willow Ufgood!

33
00:06:35.000 --> 00:06:39.000
Shhh! It's the prefect.
That's all I need.

34
00:06:39.080 --> 00:06:42.400
Keep it quiet.
Don't touch it.

35
00:06:43.880 --> 00:06:47.560
Mr. Burglekutt. my husband
hasn't stolen anything!

36
00:06:47.640 --> 00:06:49.520
Baaa!

37
00:06:52.800 --> 00:06:56.160
Ufgood. you still haven't
paid your debts to me.

38
00:06:56.240 --> 00:06:58.160
Where did you
get these seeds?

39
00:06:58.240 --> 00:07:00.880
Well. maybe I used magic.

40
00:07:00.960 --> 00:07:04.720
You're no sorcerer. Ufgood.
You're a clown.

41
00:07:04.800 --> 00:07:08.240
I sell the planting seeds around here.
Now tell me where you got them.

42
00:07:08.280 --> 00:07:11.600
My family's been gathering them
in the forest since last fall.

43
00:07:11.680 --> 00:07:14.600
- There's no law against that.

44
00:07:14.680 --> 00:07:19.640
Willow. you didn't leave
them alone by the river?

45
00:07:19.680 --> 00:07:21.920
Magic?
You'll need magic...

46
00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:24.280
if you expect to get your planting
done before the rains start.

47
00:07:26.240 --> 00:07:31.520
I will have this land. And you're
gonna end up working in the mines.

48
00:07:33.640 --> 00:07:37.240
- Baaa-

49
00:07:40.240 --> 00:07:43.120
Oh. you're lovely.

50
00:07:43.160 --> 00:07:45.080
- Yes. you are.

51
00:07:45.160 --> 00:07:49.440
- Kiaya!
- Oh. Willow!

52
00:07:49.480 --> 00:07:54.200
- Good girl. Good girl.
- Under no condition whatsoever...

53
00:07:54.280 --> 00:07:56.920
is anyone in this family
to fall in love with that baby.

54
00:07:56.960 --> 00:08:01.520
Yes. you are. Come on. Mims.
Come on. Come on.

55
00:08:01.600 --> 00:08:03.560
There we are. Come on.

56
00:08:03.640 --> 00:08:06.160
Hey. I will not be ignored!

57
00:08:06.240 --> 00:08:09.760
Mims? Ranon?

58
00:08:20.320 --> 00:08:22.360
- You're gonna be all clean.

59
00:08:28.760 --> 00:08:31.920
Willow. do you think we should
take her to the village council?

60
00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:34.480
No. No.
They'll think it's a bad omen.

61
00:08:34.560 --> 00:08:37.240
There'll be a flood or a drought.
and everyone will blame me for it.

62
00:08:37.320 --> 00:08:40.120
"Willow Ufgood brought around
that Daikini. didn't he?

63
00:08:40.160 --> 00:08:43.080
That's right. He's that
lousy farmer too. Let's get him!

64
00:08:43.160 --> 00:08:47.040
- Willow. calm down.
- Calm down?

65
00:08:47.120 --> 00:08:49.080
Kiaya. tomorrow's my big day.

66
00:08:49.160 --> 00:08:52.760
Love. the High Aldwin hasn't
picked a new apprentice in years.

67
00:08:52.800 --> 00:08:55.960
Tomorrow's gonna be different.
I just know he's gonna pick me.

68
00:08:58.600 --> 00:09:02.120
- Here. Hold her.
- Hey. no. I don't want her. Kiaya.

69
00:09:02.200 --> 00:09:04.880
- Hold her while I get some milk.
- Oh. no. no. Oh.

70
00:09:12.200 --> 00:09:15.520
- Dada. she likes you.

71
00:09:22.240 --> 00:09:23.360
- Bye.

72
00:09:23.360 --> 00:09:26.360
- Bye.

73
00:09:26.400 --> 00:09:30.160
- Come on. kids. Let's go.

74
00:09:35.960 --> 00:09:39.400
I will now magic ally join the rings!

75
00:10:00.480 --> 00:10:02.960
- Whoa-ah!

76
00:10:07.560 --> 00:10:09.880
Thank you. son.

77
00:10:09.920 --> 00:10:14.760
If you're easily shocked.
please turn away.

78
00:10:29.320 --> 00:10:31.480
Give me a ripe one. Good.

79
00:10:37.440 --> 00:10:41.760
- And now. for my final amazing feat.

80
00:10:41.840 --> 00:10:46.480
- I will make this entire pig disappear!

81
00:10:54.200 --> 00:10:59.120
- Mims. see?
- Please. watch very closely.

82
00:10:59.200 --> 00:11:04.600
- Wuppitybairn. deru. deru!

83
00:11:06.760 --> 00:11:09.080
- Well-
- What happened to your pig?

84
00:11:11.680 --> 00:11:14.600
No!
Hey. come here. you!

85
00:11:18.840 --> 00:11:22.120
I had seen enough.

86
00:11:36.600 --> 00:11:39.760
Attention!
The High Aldwin...

87
00:11:39.840 --> 00:11:42.640
-will now make his choice
for his new apprentice!
- You'll be all right.

88
00:11:42.680 --> 00:11:46.000
Bring forth the hopefuls.

89
00:11:46.080 --> 00:11:48.400
- Good luck.
- Good luck. Dada.

90
00:11:48.480 --> 00:11:52.080
Willow Ufgood. a hopeful?
How did he get picked?

91
00:11:52.160 --> 00:11:54.520
Is this a joke?

92
00:11:54.600 --> 00:11:58.880
- Willow?

93
00:12:01.200 --> 00:12:06.440
Magic is the bloodstream
of the universe!

94
00:12:06.480 --> 00:12:10.880
Forget all you know...
or think you know.

95
00:12:10.960 --> 00:12:14.800
All that your require
is your intuition.

96
00:12:14.880 --> 00:12:18.800
Now. the power
to control the world...

97
00:12:18.880 --> 00:12:23.200
is in which finger?

98
00:13:03.440 --> 00:13:07.800
- No apprentice this year!

99
00:13:27.360 --> 00:13:30.600
- Where's Mims?
- I don't know. She was right here!

100
00:13:30.680 --> 00:13:33.480
Take Ranon in there. quick!

101
00:13:41.040 --> 00:13:43.880
- Mims!

102
00:13:45.200 --> 00:13:47.240
- Mims!

103
00:13:55.160 --> 00:13:59.800
- Mims!
- Dada-

104
00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:03.960
- I'm scared. Dada!

105
00:14:13.840 --> 00:14:16.320
Come on!

106
00:14:33.240 --> 00:14:36.080
- Vohnkar!

107
00:14:45.200 --> 00:14:48.000
- Check to make sure.
- It's dead!

108
00:14:50.240 --> 00:14:51.960
Dada! Dada!

109
00:14:55.160 --> 00:14:57.320
It was looking
for somebody's baby!

110
00:15:00.240 --> 00:15:03.880
- Mommy.
- Kiaya!

111
00:15:10.960 --> 00:15:14.160
Kiaya!
Kiaya!

112
00:15:14.240 --> 00:15:17.120
- I'm here.

113
00:15:21.040 --> 00:15:24.520
- Oh. Kiaya.

114
00:15:24.600 --> 00:15:26.720
We can't keep
the baby. Kiaya.

115
00:15:26.760 --> 00:15:29.520
We have to take her
to the village council.

116
00:15:42.440 --> 00:15:47.160
Silence! One beast we can kill.
but there may be more.

117
00:15:47.240 --> 00:15:49.520
And you can be assured
that they won't give up...

118
00:15:49.600 --> 00:15:51.480
until they find what
they're looking for!

119
00:15:51.560 --> 00:15:54.680
-It's a sign!
- Who's to blame for this?

120
00:15:54.760 --> 00:15:57.160
We must find the culprit
and throw him in the pit!

121
00:15:57.200 --> 00:16:02.120
- In the pit! In the pit!

122
00:16:02.200 --> 00:16:04.240
In the pit! In the pit!

123
00:16:04.320 --> 00:16:07.480
-In the pit! In the pit!
- Willow.

124
00:16:07.560 --> 00:16:11.720
- Willow Ufgood.

125
00:16:11.800 --> 00:16:14.160
Come forward.

126
00:16:19.600 --> 00:16:24.720
My children found this baby
alone by the river. High Aldwin.

127
00:16:30.080 --> 00:16:32.160
- A Daikini child.

128
00:16:32.240 --> 00:16:35.320
That's what the beasts want.
Let's give it back to them!

129
00:16:35.400 --> 00:16:36.440
Yeah!

130
00:16:36.520 --> 00:16:39.680
- They'll kill her! You can't!
- It isn't one of us.

131
00:16:39.760 --> 00:16:42.280
This child is special!

132
00:16:42.360 --> 00:16:46.480
This child must be taken beyond
the boundaries of our village.

133
00:16:46.560 --> 00:16:49.480
All the way across
the great river...

134
00:16:49.560 --> 00:16:51.560
to the Daikini crossroads.

135
00:16:51.640 --> 00:16:56.160
- Well. who'll do that?
- It seems only fair...

136
00:16:56.200 --> 00:16:59.440
that the man to take
this baby to the crossroads...

137
00:16:59.520 --> 00:17:02.360
be the very man who
plucked it out of the river.

138
00:17:03.880 --> 00:17:06.400
- I nominate Willow Ufgood.

139
00:17:06.440 --> 00:17:08.880
No!

140
00:17:08.960 --> 00:17:12.360
I will consult the bones!

141
00:17:19.440 --> 00:17:24.720
- The bones tell me... nothing.

142
00:17:26.320 --> 00:17:30.080
Do you have any love
for this child?

143
00:17:38.160 --> 00:17:42.440
Yes. Yes. I do.

144
00:17:42.520 --> 00:17:46.760
- The bones have spoken!

145
00:17:46.800 --> 00:17:50.600
Willow Ufgood. the safety
of this village depends upon you.

146
00:17:50.680 --> 00:17:54.600
- Praise the bones!
- Praise the bones!

147
00:17:54.680 --> 00:17:57.080
But you will need help.

148
00:17:57.160 --> 00:18:02.280
Who has the courage to protect
our brave fellow on his journey?

149
00:18:04.240 --> 00:18:08.200
- I'll go with him.
- Ah. Meegosh.

150
00:18:08.240 --> 00:18:11.400
- Excellent choice.
- I'll go!

151
00:18:11.480 --> 00:18:13.840
Vohnkar! Vohnkar!

152
00:18:13.920 --> 00:18:16.520
No! Not vohnkar!
He's the best warrior in the village!

153
00:18:16.560 --> 00:18:19.640
We need him here!
Vohnkar. step back!

154
00:18:27.320 --> 00:18:29.800
All this expedition needs
is a leader.

155
00:18:29.880 --> 00:18:33.120
And according to the bones...

156
00:18:33.200 --> 00:18:36.440
- Bh-
-That leader is...

157
00:18:36.520 --> 00:18:37.880
...you. Burglekutt!

158
00:18:37.880 --> 00:18:38.840
you. Burglekutt!

159
00:18:38.920 --> 00:18:42.240
vohnkar!

160
00:18:42.320 --> 00:18:46.240
- What's your problem. son?
- How do you mean?

161
00:18:46.320 --> 00:18:51.400
When I held up my fingers
what was your first impulse?

162
00:18:51.480 --> 00:18:55.240
- Well. it was stupid.
-Just tell me.

163
00:18:55.280 --> 00:18:59.560
- To pick my own finger.
- Aha! That was the correct answer.

164
00:18:59.640 --> 00:19:04.200
You lack faith in yourself.
More than anyone in the village.

165
00:19:04.240 --> 00:19:06.760
you have the potential
to be a great sorcerer.

166
00:19:06.840 --> 00:19:11.480
Now. when you're out there.
listen to your own heart.

167
00:19:13.360 --> 00:19:18.160
- These will protect you. They're magic!
- Acorns?

168
00:19:18.240 --> 00:19:22.080
Anything you throw them at
turns to stone.

169
00:19:25.040 --> 00:19:28.120
You have much to learn.
young Ufgood.

170
00:19:40.520 --> 00:19:44.800
- Are you scared. Dada?
- No!

171
00:19:44.880 --> 00:19:48.960
Even with fairies in the woods that'll
put you to sleep for a hundred years?

172
00:19:50.880 --> 00:19:52.920
- Doesn't bother me.
- Brownies?

173
00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:55.800
- Dragons?
- Trolls?

174
00:19:55.880 --> 00:19:59.160
Trolls that'll skin you alive
and take your face off?

175
00:19:59.240 --> 00:20:02.720
Ranon!
You know I hate trolls.

176
00:20:02.760 --> 00:20:05.800
I can be your guard
and carry your spear.

177
00:20:05.840 --> 00:20:07.360
Me too. Me too. Dada.

178
00:20:08.880 --> 00:20:14.000
What a lucky father I am. I wish
I could take you bobbins with me.

179
00:20:16.960 --> 00:20:19.400
Good-bye. Dada.

180
00:20:21.360 --> 00:20:25.200
Go play!
Go on.

181
00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:32.400
We've never been apart.

182
00:20:33.400 --> 00:20:36.600
I miss you already.

183
00:20:37.880 --> 00:20:41.160
Don't worry. Kiaya.
I'll be fine.

184
00:20:41.240 --> 00:20:43.080
I'll be back
before you know it.

185
00:20:45.240 --> 00:20:47.880
Well. remember
to keep her warm.

186
00:20:49.840 --> 00:20:52.440
And... here.

187
00:20:54.480 --> 00:20:57.160
This will bring you luck.

188
00:21:09.800 --> 00:21:12.040
Good brave people!

189
00:21:13.800 --> 00:21:16.440
The outer world is
no place for a Nelwyn.

190
00:21:16.520 --> 00:21:21.040
Give the baby to the first
Daikini you see. then hurry home.

191
00:21:24.400 --> 00:21:27.840
Tuatha...
lokwathrak... tuatha!

192
00:21:27.920 --> 00:21:31.320
Going the direction the bird is flying!

193
00:21:31.400 --> 00:21:35.160
- Ooh.

194
00:21:35.240 --> 00:21:37.960
It's going back to the village!

195
00:21:39.720 --> 00:21:41.600
Ignore the bird.
Follow the river.

196
00:21:41.680 --> 00:21:43.840
Move out!

197
00:22:06.800 --> 00:22:10.120
- Hold on. Meegosh.
- What's wrong?

198
00:22:10.200 --> 00:22:14.080
- We have to stop.
- Stop? Why?

199
00:22:14.120 --> 00:22:16.520
- The baby's sick.

200
00:22:20.320 --> 00:22:24.720
She's not sick!
Let me see.

201
00:22:24.800 --> 00:22:27.880
Uhaghh!
Take her! Take her!

202
00:22:30.360 --> 00:22:33.320
She'll be fine
once she gets some rest.

203
00:22:35.560 --> 00:22:37.160
Clean me up.

204
00:22:40.680 --> 00:22:43.760
I didn't ask you
to bring me a dead nursemaid.

205
00:22:43.840 --> 00:22:47.600
-Sorsha. you're useless!
-I'm backtracking the nursemaid's trail.

206
00:22:47.640 --> 00:22:49.760
I'll find where
she hid the baby.

207
00:22:51.640 --> 00:22:53.800
Ah. General Kael. at last.

208
00:22:53.880 --> 00:22:58.400
My queen. I have destroyed
the castle at Galladoorn.

209
00:22:58.480 --> 00:23:02.040
Well done. But now I have
another task for you.

210
00:23:02.120 --> 00:23:07.360
Help my daughter to find
that tiny. helpless baby...

211
00:23:07.440 --> 00:23:09.320
that continues
somehow to elude her.

212
00:23:11.160 --> 00:23:13.040
The baby of the prophecy?

213
00:23:13.120 --> 00:23:16.400
- The one that would destroy you?
- I need that baby alive.

214
00:23:16.480 --> 00:23:18.840
I must perform
the ritual that will...

215
00:23:18.920 --> 00:23:22.120
exile the child's spirit
into oblivion.

216
00:23:22.200 --> 00:23:24.840
- Find her!
- I don't need his help. Mother.

217
00:23:24.880 --> 00:23:26.880
You'll do as I say. child.

218
00:23:33.040 --> 00:23:35.120
I read the signs.

219
00:23:35.200 --> 00:23:38.240
One day. I fear. your daughter
will betray you.

220
00:23:38.320 --> 00:23:42.320
I trust her loyalty
more than I trust yours.

221
00:23:57.400 --> 00:23:59.840
- Move!

222
00:23:59.920 --> 00:24:01.800
It's an ambush.
Come on. Move!

223
00:24:05.920 --> 00:24:09.480
- Come on!

224
00:24:18.680 --> 00:24:21.480
The Nelwyns have got the baby.
We've searched the village.

225
00:24:21.560 --> 00:24:24.400
But a group of them
Is on the road somewhere.

226
00:24:24.480 --> 00:24:26.240
They couldn' t have gone far!

227
00:24:26.280 --> 00:24:29.160
Widen the search
and report to Sorsha!

228
00:24:36.240 --> 00:24:38.840
Come. We'll keep to the woods.

229
00:25:16.040 --> 00:25:20.040
That's it!
It's the crossroads!

230
00:25:35.800 --> 00:25:38.640
Keep this fire high.
We don't know what's out there.

231
00:25:43.920 --> 00:25:46.320
- What was that?

232
00:25:47.600 --> 00:25:50.280
Get the spears!

233
00:26:06.040 --> 00:26:07.920
- Uhh. Uhh.

234
00:26:07.960 --> 00:26:11.680
Give me some water. peck.
or you die.

235
00:26:11.760 --> 00:26:14.080
Do you understand?

236
00:26:14.160 --> 00:26:15.960
- Water.
- Yeah.

237
00:26:18.000 --> 00:26:19.920
Hurry up!

238
00:26:23.760 --> 00:26:26.560
Get me some water.
you measly little pecks.

239
00:26:26.640 --> 00:26:29.960
It's a Daikini.
We're in luck.

240
00:26:30.040 --> 00:26:32.360
We can't give her to him!

241
00:26:32.400 --> 00:26:36.200
- Somebody put him there for a reason.
- We've got to get rid of her.

242
00:26:36.280 --> 00:26:38.760
- Those soldiers are after us.
- Shhh.

243
00:26:38.840 --> 00:26:41.600
He's looking right at us.

244
00:26:45.360 --> 00:26:47.280
We've got to give
that baby to somebody.

245
00:26:47.320 --> 00:26:50.080
I'm somebody.

246
00:26:50.160 --> 00:26:54.320
Let me out of here. I'll take care
of the baby.

247
00:26:56.080 --> 00:27:00.520
- I trust him completely.
- But he tried to strangle me.

248
00:27:00.560 --> 00:27:04.360
- I want to go home!
- No. Burglekutt!

249
00:27:04.440 --> 00:27:07.640
- We should wait!
- Are you challenging my authority?

250
00:27:07.720 --> 00:27:10.960
As far as this baby
is concerned... yes.

251
00:27:11.000 --> 00:27:13.920
Don't listen to him. Burglekutt.

252
00:27:14.000 --> 00:27:18.880
Fine. You stay here alone.
but we're going.

253
00:27:18.960 --> 00:27:21.080
That's a bad idea.
Very bad.

254
00:27:21.160 --> 00:27:24.440
- Dangerous out there.
- Get the gear. men.

255
00:27:24.520 --> 00:27:27.920
- vohnkar-
- It's not his decision!

256
00:27:28.000 --> 00:27:31.760
Burglekutt. you're troll dung.

257
00:27:31.840 --> 00:27:33.440
Don't let him
talk to you that way.

258
00:27:33.520 --> 00:27:35.520
Listen here. runt.

259
00:27:35.600 --> 00:27:39.400
While you're wasting time here.
your fields aren't getting planted.

260
00:27:39.480 --> 00:27:43.600
- Think about it!
- Burglekutt. I'm gonna-

261
00:27:43.680 --> 00:27:46.920
You're gonna what?

262
00:27:50.640 --> 00:27:53.120
Some day. Burglekutt.
Some day.

263
00:27:53.200 --> 00:27:55.120
Vohnkar. let's go!

264
00:27:58.640 --> 00:28:01.240
Meegosh. are you coming?

265
00:28:03.440 --> 00:28:06.880
- I'm staying.
- Come on. men.

266
00:28:06.960 --> 00:28:10.960
Burglekutt. Let me out of here.
I'll take care of the baby. I swear.

267
00:28:11.040 --> 00:28:13.600
just let me out of here.
Please!

268
00:28:13.680 --> 00:28:17.000
Vohnkar. let me borrow that spear...
just for a minute.

269
00:28:17.040 --> 00:28:19.240
Get-
Well. at least get me some water!

270
00:28:19.280 --> 00:28:24.040
Burglekutt. don't leave me alone
with these two!

271
00:28:24.120 --> 00:28:28.720
- What'll we do now. Willow?

272
00:28:28.800 --> 00:28:31.320
Well. that was really stupid. peck.

273
00:28:31.400 --> 00:28:36.000
- Don't call me a peck.
- Oh. I'm sorry... peck.

274
00:28:36.080 --> 00:28:39.680
- Peck. peck. peck. peck.
- You be careful!

275
00:28:39.760 --> 00:28:43.360
I'm a powerful sorcerer.
See this acorn?

276
00:28:44.720 --> 00:28:49.040
- I'll throw it. and turn you to stone.
- Whoo-

277
00:28:49.120 --> 00:28:51.000
I'm really scared.

278
00:28:51.040 --> 00:28:53.800
No. don't! Don't!

279
00:28:53.840 --> 00:28:56.560
There's a peck here
with an acorn pointed at me!

280
00:28:56.640 --> 00:28:59.200
Oh. I wouldn't
want to waste it.

281
00:28:59.280 --> 00:29:02.400
Ha!
Peck. peck. peck. peck.

282
00:29:02.480 --> 00:29:04.920
peck. peck. peck.
peck. peck!

283
00:29:32.360 --> 00:29:35.120
- What was that?

284
00:29:38.360 --> 00:29:41.920
Mornin'. boys.

285
00:29:42.000 --> 00:29:45.960
Rough night last night.
wasn't it?

286
00:29:46.000 --> 00:29:49.240
I don't think I introduced
myself yesterday.

287
00:29:49.320 --> 00:29:52.640
My name is Madmartigan.
and you are. uh-

288
00:29:52.720 --> 00:29:55.560
No. Meegosh.
Don't go near him.

289
00:29:55.600 --> 00:29:58.920
- He's dangerous.
- I am not.

290
00:29:58.960 --> 00:30:01.040
Good.

291
00:30:05.600 --> 00:30:07.800
Stop! Wait!

292
00:30:09.480 --> 00:30:12.120
- Whoa!

293
00:30:17.360 --> 00:30:21.680
- What's going on?
- Smells like a battle.

294
00:30:21.760 --> 00:30:24.160
I suppose you're a warrior.

295
00:30:24.240 --> 00:30:26.640
I am the greatest swordsman
that ever lived.

296
00:30:26.720 --> 00:30:29.440
Humph.

297
00:30:29.520 --> 00:30:33.120
Say. uh- Could I have
some of that water?

298
00:30:42.440 --> 00:30:47.000
I don't know why I try.

299
00:30:51.600 --> 00:30:54.720
I guess I am gonna die here.
Who cares.

300
00:30:54.800 --> 00:30:56.640
- Here.
- Thanks. friend. Oh!

301
00:30:56.720 --> 00:30:59.000
- What's that?

302
00:30:59.080 --> 00:31:02.880
I'd say
two or three hundred horses.

303
00:31:02.960 --> 00:31:06.760
five or six wagons...
and about a thousand fools.

304
00:31:09.360 --> 00:31:13.000
- Thank you. Ohh-
- Come on. Meegosh.

305
00:31:17.160 --> 00:31:20.720
It's gonna be
all right. little bobbin.

306
00:31:26.440 --> 00:31:30.200
- Everything's gonna be all right.

307
00:31:33.400 --> 00:31:36.360
- Excuse me. sir.
- Out of the way. peck!

308
00:31:38.240 --> 00:31:40.520
Uh. pardon me.

309
00:31:40.560 --> 00:31:42.600
Uh-

310
00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:53.000
Excuse me. sir. We found one
of your babies in our village.

311
00:31:53.080 --> 00:31:55.880
Will you please
take care of her?

312
00:31:55.960 --> 00:32:00.200
We're going into battle. little ones.
Find a woman to take care of her.

313
00:32:01.560 --> 00:32:04.600
They thought you were
a woman. Airk.

314
00:32:04.680 --> 00:32:06.960
Well-

315
00:32:07.040 --> 00:32:11.400
-Madmartigan. what did you do this time?
-Nothing you wouldn't have done.

316
00:32:11.480 --> 00:32:13.760
I always knew
you'd end up in a crow's cage.

317
00:32:13.840 --> 00:32:15.600
At least I'm not
down there herding sheep.

318
00:32:15.680 --> 00:32:17.120
What are you doing this far north?

319
00:32:17.200 --> 00:32:19.120
The Nockmaar army
destroyed Galladoorn.

320
00:32:20.080 --> 00:32:21.360
The castle?

321
00:32:21.400 --> 00:32:23.760
Bavmorda's troops are
crushing everything in sight.

322
00:32:23.840 --> 00:32:25.680
Come on.
Let me out of here. Airk.

323
00:32:25.760 --> 00:32:27.920
Give me a sword.
I'll win this war for you.

324
00:32:28.040 --> 00:32:32.160
Madmartigan-
I still serve Galladoorn.

325
00:32:32.240 --> 00:32:34.120
You serve no one.

326
00:32:34.200 --> 00:32:36.360
Remember?

327
00:32:36.440 --> 00:32:39.520
Sit in your coffin and rot.

328
00:32:39.600 --> 00:32:42.520
- Hyah!
- Wait. Airk. You need me!

329
00:32:42.600 --> 00:32:44.920
I'll be around
long after you're dead!

330
00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:47.520
When I get out of here.
I'm gonna cut your head off...

331
00:32:47.600 --> 00:32:49.600
and stick it
on a pig pole!

332
00:33:06.400 --> 00:33:10.920
- I miss Kiaya and the bobbins.

333
00:33:14.760 --> 00:33:18.400
We're running out of food.

334
00:33:18.480 --> 00:33:21.960
Nobody's gonna
take care of that baby.

335
00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:24.880
You know why?
Nobody cares.

336
00:33:27.640 --> 00:33:31.040
Except me.

337
00:33:31.120 --> 00:33:35.160
You want to go back to your families.
I want out of this cage.

338
00:33:35.240 --> 00:33:39.040
Let me take care of that baby.
I'll look after her like she was my own.

339
00:33:39.120 --> 00:33:41.960
I believe he would. Willow.

340
00:33:42.040 --> 00:33:44.480
He doesn't know
anything about babies.

341
00:33:44.560 --> 00:33:49.560
Right. But I know
a lot of women who do.

342
00:33:49.640 --> 00:33:52.440
If I had somebody in my life.

343
00:33:52.520 --> 00:33:55.960
a little daughter. perhaps.

344
00:33:56.040 --> 00:33:59.160
I might have a reason
to go on living.

345
00:34:02.280 --> 00:34:04.960
You can't leave me
in here to die.

346
00:34:05.040 --> 00:34:07.960
Not when all I want
to do is protect her.

347
00:34:20.720 --> 00:34:24.480
I feel better!

348
00:34:24.560 --> 00:34:28.120
-You've done the right thing! -Okay. All right. All right.

349
00:34:28.200 --> 00:34:32.480
- You gotta promise to feed her.
- Come to Daddy. little darlin'.

350
00:34:32.560 --> 00:34:37.360
- And keep her clean.
- Absolutely.

351
00:34:37.440 --> 00:34:39.400
- Hee. hee. hee!

352
00:34:39.480 --> 00:34:44.160
- Wheee!

353
00:34:44.240 --> 00:34:47.360
She likes me.

354
00:34:49.360 --> 00:34:51.640
Here are her changing rags.

355
00:34:51.720 --> 00:34:53.840
- And her milk bladder.
- Any milk in there?

356
00:34:53.880 --> 00:34:58.000
- It's for her!
- I wouldn't steal from a baby.

357
00:34:59.640 --> 00:35:03.040
- You wory too much. peck.

358
00:35:03.120 --> 00:35:06.880
- It's Willow.
- I mean Willow.

359
00:35:06.960 --> 00:35:12.480
Now listen. boys- Willow.
You've done the right thing.

360
00:35:12.560 --> 00:35:15.800
And I want you to get home
and bring your crop in.

361
00:35:22.040 --> 00:35:26.120
- Good-bye. little one.

362
00:35:34.480 --> 00:35:36.640
Please. take good care of her.

363
00:35:38.360 --> 00:35:41.080
I give you my word of honor!

364
00:35:47.480 --> 00:35:51.240
- Meegosh. slow down!
- Oh. come on!

365
00:35:51.280 --> 00:35:55.360
If we hurry. we can be home by
tomorrow morning. We'll be heroes.

366
00:35:55.440 --> 00:35:58.800
- Do you really think so?
- Sure.

367
00:35:58.880 --> 00:36:01.040
"Look. there's
Willow and Meegosh.

368
00:36:01.120 --> 00:36:03.240
The heroes have come home."

369
00:36:03.320 --> 00:36:06.280
"Welcome back. boys.
You deserve medals!"

370
00:36:06.360 --> 00:36:10.440
- Yeah. Medals.

371
00:36:10.480 --> 00:36:14.080
Meegosh-

372
00:36:15.880 --> 00:36:19.840
- Did we do the right thing?
- Absolutely.

373
00:36:19.920 --> 00:36:24.040
- There's nothing to wory about.

374
00:36:26.920 --> 00:36:29.120
Hyah! Ha!

375
00:36:29.200 --> 00:36:34.200
I stole the baby! I stole the baby!

376
00:36:34.280 --> 00:36:37.880
- Hyah!
- That's my baby!

377
00:36:37.960 --> 00:36:39.840
- Stop! Wait! Come back!

378
00:36:39.920 --> 00:36:42.960
Left. you stupid bird.
Left! Ha ha!

379
00:36:45.640 --> 00:36:48.760
- Ah!
- Ow!

380
00:36:48.840 --> 00:36:52.360
Brownies!
Let's get out of here!

381
00:36:52.440 --> 00:36:55.640
- Come on. Meegosh!
- Ow!

382
00:36:56.600 --> 00:37:00.200
- Uhh-uh-huh-uh.
- Uhh. Oww!

383
00:37:01.440 --> 00:37:03.400
We'll outrun 'em!

384
00:37:07.960 --> 00:37:11.880
-Hey. ugly. wake up!-

385
00:37:11.960 --> 00:37:14.320
Huh?

386
00:37:14.360 --> 00:37:19.280
- Stand your ground. He's our prisoner.

387
00:37:19.320 --> 00:37:22.000
Meegosh.
where's the baby?

388
00:37:22.040 --> 00:37:23.920
Bring the Nelwyns tome.

389
00:37:23.960 --> 00:37:25.320
All right. you heard her!

390
00:37:25.400 --> 00:37:29.040
- What's going on?
- Shut up. or I'll break your nose.

391
00:37:29.080 --> 00:37:31.360
You are mine to toy with.

392
00:37:31.440 --> 00:37:34.800
Forward!

393
00:37:34.880 --> 00:37:38.520
- Gimme the rope.

394
00:37:38.600 --> 00:37:42.440
Where-
Where...

395
00:37:42.520 --> 00:37:44.720
did you get that baby?

396
00:37:44.760 --> 00:37:49.320
I stole it from a stupid Daikini.

397
00:37:49.480 --> 00:37:52.520
Franjean. release the Nelwyns.

398
00:37:52.560 --> 00:37:56.680
-And stop pestering them.
- Uh-oh.

399
00:37:56.760 --> 00:37:58.760
Ahh-

400
00:38:00.920 --> 00:38:02.800
- Yaah!

401
00:38:06.880 --> 00:38:10.000
- You!

402
00:38:10.040 --> 00:38:14.920
Welcome to my kingdom.

403
00:38:20.840 --> 00:38:25.160
- I'm happy to meet you. Willow Ufgood.
- How do you know my name?

404
00:38:25.240 --> 00:38:28.360
Blora Danan told me.

405
00:38:28.400 --> 00:38:31.600
Blora?
Blora. Willow is here.

406
00:38:34.280 --> 00:38:39.600
- But she's just a baby.
- She's very special.

407
00:38:39.680 --> 00:38:44.800
My Brownies have been searching for her
ever since we heard she was born.

408
00:38:44.880 --> 00:38:49.600
Blora Danan has chosen you
to be her guardian.

409
00:38:49.680 --> 00:38:54.240
- Me?
- Yes. She likes you.

410
00:38:55.600 --> 00:39:00.360
And Elora Danan knows you
have the courage to help us.

411
00:39:00.440 --> 00:39:03.880
Take my wand
to the sorceress. Find Raziel.

412
00:39:03.960 --> 00:39:08.040
She will guide you and Blora Danan
to the kingdom of Tir Asleen.

413
00:39:08.080 --> 00:39:11.080
where a good king and queen
will look after her.

414
00:39:11.120 --> 00:39:14.760
You need a warrior for
a job like this. I'm a nobody.

415
00:39:14.920 --> 00:39:18.040
Blora. you don't want me.

416
00:39:18.120 --> 00:39:21.680
Tell her.
I'm short. even for a Nelwyn.

417
00:39:24.520 --> 00:39:27.040
Hello?

418
00:39:34.080 --> 00:39:37.360
Blora Danan must survive!

419
00:39:37.400 --> 00:39:42.080
She must fulfill her destiny and bring
about the downfall of Queen Bavmorda.

420
00:39:42.120 --> 00:39:44.880
whose powers are growing
like an evil plague.

421
00:39:44.920 --> 00:39:49.120
Unless she is stopped.
Bavmorda will control the lives...

422
00:39:49.160 --> 00:39:53.560
of your village.
your children- everyone.

423
00:39:58.040 --> 00:40:01.400
All creatures of good heart
need your help. Willow.

424
00:40:01.480 --> 00:40:06.480
The choice is yours.

425
00:40:28.120 --> 00:40:32.200
- Hey. Meegosh. Wake up.
- Huh?

426
00:40:32.240 --> 00:40:36.320
- It's time to go home.
- Home?

427
00:40:38.800 --> 00:40:42.200
Listen. Meegosh.
Tell Kiaya I love her.

428
00:40:42.280 --> 00:40:46.640
- And I think of her every day.
- Willow-

429
00:40:46.720 --> 00:40:50.040
And tell her I'm not going to let
anything happen to the baby.

430
00:40:50.120 --> 00:40:52.640
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

431
00:40:52.720 --> 00:40:55.520
I hope so.

432
00:40:55.600 --> 00:40:59.040
Listen. be careful.

433
00:41:04.880 --> 00:41:09.240
- I know the way. Franjean.
- You always think you know the way.

434
00:41:09.320 --> 00:41:12.640
-I am the leader!
- How long will it take to find Raziel?

435
00:41:12.720 --> 00:41:17.000
Um. not long. She's been exiled
to an island just over those hills.

436
00:41:17.080 --> 00:41:20.040
- She's what?
- Exiled...

437
00:41:20.120 --> 00:41:23.800
by the evil Queen Bavmorda.

438
00:41:23.880 --> 00:41:26.400
Rool. You fool. He does
not need to know everything.

439
00:41:26.480 --> 00:41:28.960
- I didn't tell him everything.
- You told him enough.

440
00:41:29.040 --> 00:41:31.240
- You mentioned the island. the queen.
- Wait a minute.

441
00:41:31.280 --> 00:41:33.840
So?

442
00:41:33.920 --> 00:41:36.600
What do you mean? What are
you saying. mysterious island?

443
00:41:36.680 --> 00:41:39.200
Don't play with that wand.

444
00:41:39.240 --> 00:41:41.720
Cherlindrea told you
it holds vast powers.

445
00:41:41.800 --> 00:41:44.160
Only a great sorcerer can use it.

446
00:41:44.240 --> 00:41:46.880
-Not a stupid peck like you.

447
00:41:46.920 --> 00:41:49.960
- This way.
- No. No. No. I don't think so.

448
00:41:50.040 --> 00:41:52.240
- All right. then this way.
- Bah. nope.

449
00:41:52.320 --> 00:41:54.720
- This way.
- This way?

450
00:41:54.800 --> 00:41:58.400
- That's what I said.
- This way.

451
00:41:58.440 --> 00:42:01.760
- You know where you're going?
- Of course.

452
00:42:01.840 --> 00:42:04.440
With us as your guides
no harm with befall you.

453
00:42:14.440 --> 00:42:18.440
- Take it up!

454
00:42:19.880 --> 00:42:23.960
- We are not going in there!
- But Blora needs fresh milk.

455
00:42:24.040 --> 00:42:28.680
- And we are drenched.
- You are not in command. shorty. I am!

456
00:42:28.760 --> 00:42:32.200
- You hear me?
- Whoa!

457
00:43:08.400 --> 00:43:10.760
- Excuse me? Excuse me.

458
00:43:10.800 --> 00:43:13.640
Could you spare some milk
for this poor. hungry baby?

459
00:43:13.720 --> 00:43:15.520
Get out of here. peck!

460
00:43:15.600 --> 00:43:17.840
Get outta here
or we'll cook ya!

461
00:43:30.680 --> 00:43:34.440
Ooh. look at her!

462
00:43:34.480 --> 00:43:36.680
I could use
a love potion on her!

463
00:43:36.720 --> 00:43:40.400
Franjean! Hey! Give me that
dust of broken heart.

464
00:43:40.480 --> 00:43:42.120
- Come on! Give it to me!
- Let go of me!

465
00:43:42.200 --> 00:43:45.440
It's very dangerous.
It belongs to the fairies!

466
00:43:49.440 --> 00:43:51.360
Hey. quiet!
You want to get us killed?

467
00:43:58.040 --> 00:44:01.640
Oh. Rool! Always playing
with those fairy love potions.

468
00:44:03.840 --> 00:44:08.760
You are so beautiful!

469
00:44:08.840 --> 00:44:12.320
- Your eyes! Your whiskers!

470
00:44:12.400 --> 00:44:14.920
- I have to kiss you!
-Rool!

471
00:44:15.000 --> 00:44:16.680
That dust of broken heart!

472
00:44:30.920 --> 00:44:33.040
Beer!

473
00:44:36.040 --> 00:44:38.080
These people are crazy!
This could be bad!

474
00:44:42.480 --> 00:44:44.400
Hurry! Hurry!

475
00:44:44.480 --> 00:44:46.280
My husband's coming!

476
00:44:46.360 --> 00:44:48.320
If he catches you here.
he'll kill us both!

477
00:44:48.400 --> 00:44:50.920
- How do I look?
- Not you!

478
00:44:52.080 --> 00:44:53.920
Where the hell
did you come from?

479
00:44:54.000 --> 00:44:56.160
I knew I shouldn't
have trusted you.

480
00:44:56.200 --> 00:44:59.880
Don't I know you?
I stole the baby from you. Daikini.

481
00:44:59.960 --> 00:45:02.080
- While you were taking a pee-pee!
- Cover your face!

482
00:45:02.160 --> 00:45:05.640
- You are crawling with Brownies.
- I hate Brownies!

483
00:45:05.680 --> 00:45:08.400
Whoa!

484
00:45:08.480 --> 00:45:10.960
- Where is he? Where?
- Hello. dear.

485
00:45:11.040 --> 00:45:13.320
There's nobody here but
me and. uh. my. uh-

486
00:45:13.360 --> 00:45:15.680
- I'll kill him!
- ...my cousin. Hilda.

487
00:45:15.760 --> 00:45:17.920
- Hilda?
- Hilda.

488
00:45:17.960 --> 00:45:20.000
- Oh. Hilda!
- This is my husband. Llug.

489
00:45:20.080 --> 00:45:22.720
- Mmm... Big husband.
- Yes.

490
00:45:22.800 --> 00:45:24.560
- How do you do?

491
00:45:24.640 --> 00:45:26.920
Hilda! Ooh.

492
00:45:26.960 --> 00:45:29.000
Come on. girly.
Don't be shy.

493
00:45:29.080 --> 00:45:31.600
- Hey! Give her back!

494
00:45:31.680 --> 00:45:33.960
- Pecks make terrible nursemaids.
- Nursemaid?

495
00:45:34.040 --> 00:45:36.840
- They get too excited.

496
00:45:36.880 --> 00:45:39.400
Excuse me!
Are we having a party?

497
00:45:39.480 --> 00:45:41.440
- Huh?
- Hey. hey. hey. hey!

498
00:45:41.520 --> 00:45:45.960
- Stop. please. Ooh.

499
00:45:46.040 --> 00:45:47.840
Come on.
Fight like a man!

500
00:45:47.880 --> 00:45:50.800
- Want to breed?

501
00:45:50.880 --> 00:45:53.760
Tempting. but no.

502
00:45:56.560 --> 00:45:58.440
Thank you.
Time to leave.

503
00:45:58.480 --> 00:46:00.360
- Bye. Hilda!
- Take them out.

504
00:46:00.400 --> 00:46:03.440
- Hey! Come along!

505
00:46:03.520 --> 00:46:06.000
- Careful. you lout!
- Move along!

506
00:46:06.080 --> 00:46:08.680
Gather pall these babies.

507
00:46:08.760 --> 00:46:10.920
That baby over there.
Let me see its arm.

508
00:46:14.520 --> 00:46:16.560
That's not the one.

509
00:46:20.120 --> 00:46:22.760
You! Are you the mother
of that child?

510
00:46:22.840 --> 00:46:25.320
- Yes. Yes. I am.
- Let me see it.

511
00:46:25.400 --> 00:46:26.920
No! Don't let her!

512
00:46:27.000 --> 00:46:28.400
Aah!

513
00:46:28.480 --> 00:46:31.240
I gave you an order. woman!

514
00:46:40.200 --> 00:46:43.520
You-
You're... beautiful.

515
00:46:43.600 --> 00:46:46.800
- And you're very strong.
- Thank you.

516
00:46:49.280 --> 00:46:51.680
You're no woman!

517
00:46:51.760 --> 00:46:53.520
- Now. honey. take it easy.
- Not a woman?

518
00:46:53.600 --> 00:46:56.360
- Gentlemen.
- Not a woman?

519
00:46:56.400 --> 00:46:59.080
- Meet Llug.

520
00:47:00.320 --> 00:47:02.280
- After them!
- Out of the way!

521
00:47:08.320 --> 00:47:09.520
- To the horses!

522
00:47:09.520 --> 00:47:10.560
- To the horses!

523
00:47:13.000 --> 00:47:15.360
Hey! What are you doing?

524
00:47:19.560 --> 00:47:21.400
- Hyah!

525
00:47:21.480 --> 00:47:25.240
Madmartigan!
Madmartigan! Wait!

526
00:47:28.560 --> 00:47:33.240
- He's not a woman!
- To your horses! Hyah! Hyah!

527
00:47:33.320 --> 00:47:35.600
Don't let them get away!

528
00:47:37.200 --> 00:47:40.480
- Madmartigan. stop!
- What?

529
00:47:51.800 --> 00:47:53.760
Hyah!

530
00:47:58.680 --> 00:48:01.080
Madmartigan.
I'm warning you-

531
00:48:03.040 --> 00:48:06.560
- Ow!
- Prepare to die!

532
00:48:29.000 --> 00:48:31.240
Madmartigan!
Stop!

533
00:49:00.080 --> 00:49:02.040
Franjean. help me!

534
00:49:06.480 --> 00:49:08.320
- Rool!
- Help!

535
00:49:08.400 --> 00:49:11.320
Rool! Rool.

536
00:49:12.440 --> 00:49:16.080
- Rool! What are you doing?
- Help me!

537
00:49:21.240 --> 00:49:23.400
- Come on. I am.
- Pull me in.

538
00:49:23.480 --> 00:49:25.840
Yeah. pull!

539
00:49:43.280 --> 00:49:45.200
You can't have her!

540
00:49:50.880 --> 00:49:52.520
Whoa!

541
00:49:57.040 --> 00:50:00.480
- Rool. this isn't funny!

542
00:50:00.560 --> 00:50:02.400
Help me cut the rope!

543
00:50:15.040 --> 00:50:17.680
Who-oa!

544
00:50:38.320 --> 00:50:40.800
Willow. stay down!

545
00:50:44.360 --> 00:50:46.320
Whoa!

546
00:50:46.360 --> 00:50:48.520
Whoa!

547
00:50:48.600 --> 00:50:50.440
Gone crazy?

548
00:50:50.520 --> 00:50:52.560
You can't chase around
with Elora like this.

549
00:50:52.640 --> 00:50:54.960
- We're getting off!
- Hyah!

550
00:50:55.000 --> 00:50:57.520
Oh! Hold on! Hyah!

551
00:51:19.400 --> 00:51:21.800
Whoa! Whoa!

552
00:51:24.840 --> 00:51:27.080
- Oh. Rool.

553
00:51:27.160 --> 00:51:30.680
Now we stop. peck.

554
00:51:30.760 --> 00:51:35.840
Stupid Daikini.
Ask him to stop the wagon.

555
00:51:35.880 --> 00:51:39.920
Madmartigan! You never. ever
drive that fast with an infant!

556
00:51:41.360 --> 00:51:43.760
I just saved that infant's life!

557
00:51:45.160 --> 00:51:47.400
Hah! Hah!

558
00:51:47.480 --> 00:51:49.360
Gather your wits. Come on.

559
00:51:49.400 --> 00:51:52.320
- Don't wory about me.
-Come on!

560
00:51:53.360 --> 00:51:55.440
- Get down!

561
00:51:55.520 --> 00:51:57.800
Uh. where am I?
Oh!

562
00:51:59.640 --> 00:52:01.640
Rool. you fool.
get out of the road!

563
00:52:17.480 --> 00:52:19.960
-Ah. Franjean!
- You better clear out. Willow.

564
00:52:20.040 --> 00:52:21.440
Before those troops come back.

565
00:52:21.480 --> 00:52:24.800
- Ah. my head!
- We don't need him. Blora.

566
00:52:32.880 --> 00:52:34.880
Madmartigan. wait!

567
00:52:34.920 --> 00:52:38.120
Go home. Willow!
It's a dangerous world.

568
00:52:38.200 --> 00:52:40.080
Yeah. and that's why
we need your help.

569
00:52:40.160 --> 00:52:43.240
My help? What do you need my help for?

570
00:52:43.320 --> 00:52:45.400
You're a sorcerer!

571
00:52:45.480 --> 00:52:48.560
You're a great warrior.
and a swordsman.

572
00:52:48.640 --> 00:52:51.400
And you're ten times
bigger than I am. stupid!

573
00:52:51.480 --> 00:52:54.600
Are you tying to make my life
more difficult than it already is?

574
00:52:57.720 --> 00:53:02.440
- Hurry! Big dogs!

575
00:53:02.520 --> 00:53:06.600
Look. I'm sorry
I got angry.

576
00:53:06.640 --> 00:53:08.520
We wouldn't have
escaped without you.

577
00:53:22.120 --> 00:53:24.840
Well. don't expect me
to help you again.

578
00:53:26.280 --> 00:53:29.760
Good! Then we go that way!
To the lake!

579
00:53:30.760 --> 00:53:33.800
That way.

580
00:53:33.840 --> 00:53:37.320
You are drunk. and when you
are drunk you forget that...

581
00:53:37.400 --> 00:53:39.240
- I am in charge!
- You are in charge.

582
00:53:39.320 --> 00:53:41.440
Fine.
Then which way do we go?

583
00:53:41.520 --> 00:53:43.440
That way!

584
00:53:46.360 --> 00:53:50.720
Oh. no!
That's the way I'm going.

585
00:53:50.760 --> 00:53:53.640
All right. all right. You can
follow me as far as the lake.

586
00:53:53.720 --> 00:53:55.840
But that's it!

587
00:53:55.880 --> 00:53:59.520
- You're not going south. are you?
- No. just as far as the lake.

588
00:53:59.560 --> 00:54:04.520
Good. Mumbo-Jumbo. I am hungry.
Go and get me some eggs or something.

589
00:54:04.600 --> 00:54:07.120
- We are not afraid of you!
- Now!

590
00:54:13.560 --> 00:54:18.040
Kael. have you found the child?

591
00:54:18.120 --> 00:54:19.800
The search goes on. my queen.

592
00:54:20.840 --> 00:54:22.760
Why. with my powers.

593
00:54:22.840 --> 00:54:25.920
with the strength
of my great army.

594
00:54:26.000 --> 00:54:29.280
can you not find
one little child?

595
00:54:29.320 --> 00:54:31.560
We look even now.
It won't be long.

596
00:54:31.640 --> 00:54:34.880
Find the child.
Find the child!

597
00:54:34.920 --> 00:54:37.440
Time is running out.

598
00:54:41.440 --> 00:54:45.680
- Good night.

599
00:54:45.720 --> 00:54:48.920
She is kinda cute.

600
00:54:49.000 --> 00:54:50.680
When she's quiet.

601
00:54:52.040 --> 00:54:53.880
She's really a princess.

602
00:54:53.960 --> 00:54:57.800
Really?
And you're a great sorcerer.

603
00:54:57.880 --> 00:54:59.720
And I'm the king of Cashmere.

604
00:54:59.800 --> 00:55:03.440
Go to sleep. Willow.

605
00:55:03.520 --> 00:55:05.920
Good night. Madmartigan.

606
00:55:05.960 --> 00:55:08.840
Rats! Big rats! Rats!

607
00:55:08.880 --> 00:55:12.080
Uh- Uh! Oh!
Rats! Ra-

608
00:55:12.160 --> 00:55:14.960
Oh. Rool. you had
that stupid rat dream!

609
00:55:25.320 --> 00:55:27.920
Tuatha...

610
00:55:28.000 --> 00:55:30.080
Lawkathok...

611
00:55:30.160 --> 00:55:32.000
- Tuatha!

612
00:55:32.040 --> 00:55:34.680
Huh?
Willow?

613
00:55:35.720 --> 00:55:37.760
Willow?

614
00:55:39.440 --> 00:55:41.800
Oh. There you are.

615
00:55:41.880 --> 00:55:43.760
Madmartigan!

616
00:55:43.840 --> 00:55:47.040
'Night. Willow.

617
00:55:58.640 --> 00:56:00.560
This way! This way!

618
00:56:11.880 --> 00:56:13.760
What are you doing?

619
00:56:13.800 --> 00:56:16.080
I found some black root.
She loves it!

620
00:56:16.160 --> 00:56:18.960
Black root? I am
the father of two children.

621
00:56:19.040 --> 00:56:20.960
and you never. ever
give a baby black root.

622
00:56:21.120 --> 00:56:24.040
Well. my mother
raised us on black root.

623
00:56:24.120 --> 00:56:26.560
It's good for ya!
It puts hair on your chest.

624
00:56:26.640 --> 00:56:29.280
- Doesn't it. Sticks?
- Her name is not Sticks.

625
00:56:29.320 --> 00:56:32.160
She's Blora Danan.
the future empress of Tir Asleen.

626
00:56:32.200 --> 00:56:34.440
And the last thing she's gonna
want is a hairy chest!

627
00:56:38.440 --> 00:56:40.400
Did you see what he did?

628
00:56:40.480 --> 00:56:43.600
He stole our black root. I'll get
some more. don't wory about it.

629
00:56:48.240 --> 00:56:51.440
- There it is! The island!

630
00:56:53.560 --> 00:56:55.400
We made it.

631
00:56:55.480 --> 00:56:59.840
We have led you to
the island of the sorceress Fin Raziel.

632
00:56:59.920 --> 00:57:04.000
- We'll get a boat in that village.
- A big boat.

633
00:57:21.320 --> 00:57:23.240
Well. looks like
I got you here.

634
00:57:23.320 --> 00:57:25.680
You!
What did you do?

635
00:57:25.760 --> 00:57:28.640
All you did was hang around
and eat our eggs! Huh?

636
00:57:28.720 --> 00:57:30.600
I found a boat.
We're all set.

637
00:57:30.680 --> 00:57:34.440
Good. Take these two lizards
out and drown them.

638
00:57:34.520 --> 00:57:37.720
- Who are you calling lizards?
- Heh? Heh?

639
00:57:39.720 --> 00:57:42.280
Your mother was lizard!

640
00:57:45.160 --> 00:57:47.560
- Good-bye. Sticks.

641
00:57:50.120 --> 00:57:52.920
If you really are a princess.

642
00:57:53.000 --> 00:57:55.840
take care of him.

643
00:58:01.920 --> 00:58:05.080
- Madmartigan!
- What?

644
00:58:05.160 --> 00:58:06.960
Thanks.

645
00:58:16.080 --> 00:58:18.520
Hey! Aah!

646
00:58:18.560 --> 00:58:21.800
-Keep walkin'. hero!
- Don't even turnaround!

